# The old aitc framework checkout also lives here; ignore it like aisf.
/aitc/
# The aisf framework is its own nested repo; the workspace repo ignores it
# entirely so the two never entangle.
/aisf/
# The whole /state/ tree is machine-local EXCEPT settled.db -- the one
# durable, portable file (freshness baselines, verified pass-state, and the
# scenario ledger), carried across push/pull so a fresh machine knows the
# settled work is settled and skips it. Its WAL sidecars (settled.db-wal/-shm)
# stay ignored under the broad /state/* rule; the pre-commit hook installed by
# init-git.py checkpoints the WAL into the main file before staging.
# Use /state/* (ignore the directory's contents), not /state/ (ignore the
# directory itself): git cannot re-include a file under an excluded directory,
# so /state/ + !/state/settled.db would silently drop settled.db.
/state/*
!/state/settled.db
/tools/
/reports/
/babysit-loop.out
/tmp/
/STOP.flag
/orchestrator.log
/orchestrator.log.*

# Generated final artifacts are intentionally kept at the outer workspace root,
# not inside ./proj/. Adjust this if the product's release policy changes.
/released/

# Local agent instructions and credentials
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/CODEX.md
/.claude/
/creds/
/.env
/.env.local
/.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
secrets.json
credentials.json

